  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Patriot Act provisions\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Financial institution reporting obligations\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Internal control systems\n- Regular auditing\n\n6. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have unique implementation approaches\n- Varying severity of legal consequences\n- Specific regulatory frameworks\n\n7. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial crime units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Specialized investigative departments\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes involving illegal fund transfers and disguising the origins of criminal proceeds.",
